definition: the West/abbr. for Spain 西班牙[Xi1 ban1 ya2]/Spanish
flat/level/equal/to tie (make the same score)/to draw (score)/calm/peaceful/see also 平聲|平声[ping2 sheng1]

sentences.english: Westpac Bank has recovered all but NZ$3.8 million.
sentences.chinese: 西太平洋銀行僅挽回了380萬新西蘭元的損失。

sentences.english: Okhotsk Sea is the northernmost one in the marginal seas of Pacific Ocean.
sentences.chinese: 鄂霍茨克海位於西太平洋邊緣海最北部。

sentences.english: This is the first time in five years the aircraft carrier to the Western Pacific Ocean.
sentences.chinese: 這是該航母五年來首次前往西太平洋海域。

sentences.english: During La Niña years, the Eastern Pacific is cooler than average, while the western Pacific Ocean (by Asia) is warmer.
sentences.chinese: 拉尼娜發生時東太平洋比往常更冷，西太平洋則更暖。

sentences.english: The western Pacific island of Guam held Democratic Party caucuses on Saturday.
sentences.chinese: 西太平洋上的關島在星期六舉行了民主黨黨團大會。

sentences.english: Can China Drive the U. S. Out of the West Pacific?
sentences.chinese: 中國能把美國趕出西太平洋嗎？

sentences.english: Dr Shin's four priority areas of work in the Western Pacific Region are as follows.
sentences.chinese: 申博士在西太平洋區域的四大重點工作領域如下。

sentences.english: Pacific Western University later changed its name to California Miramar University.
sentences.chinese: 西太平洋大學後來改名加州米拉馬大學。

sentences.english: The winter in Nanyue is colder while the subtropical high is stronger, and vice versa.
sentences.chinese: 西太平洋副熱帶高壓與南嶽冬季氣溫密切相關。

sentences.english: The western Pacific warm pool is mainly contributed by zonal temperature advection.
sentences.chinese: 在赤道西太平洋暖池，溫度的緯向對流有很大的貢獻。

sentences.english: At Eniwetok Atoll , in the Pacific, the USA detonated the first hydrogen bomb.
sentences.chinese: 美國在西太平洋珊瑚礁埃尼威托克島試爆第一顆氫彈。
